	<div id="p210726" class="post row-fluid odd">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2314&amp;sid=647629669c129e2dd60d55ec27089642">Burngate</a></strong> &raquo; Wed Nov 07, 2012 10:20 am </div>

			

			<div class="content">The Pi on its own can only drive one screen - be it HDMI or composite.<br />There are USB screens, which may interface with the Pi.<br /><br />A maybe better alternative would be two Pis networked together.<br />If you don't supply a mouse and keyboard for the second Pi, then that one can only be watched!</div>

			<div id="sig210726" class="signature">Brain surgery is easier than psychoanalysis</div>

		</div>

		
