	<div id="p210736" class="post row-fluid even online">
	
		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=14062&amp;sid=647629669c129e2dd60d55ec27089642" style="color: #00AA00;" class="username-coloured">mahjongg</a></strong> &raquo; Wed Nov 07, 2012 10:35 am </div>

			

			<div class="content">The raspberry PI foundation is working on an interface that would make it possible to add an LCD panel, and this panel will indeed be useable as a seconds screen, independent of the HDMI screen. The interface connector is located above the SD-Card slot, a second similar connector is for a planned camera module.</div>

			

		</div>

		
