		<div class="postbody span9">
			

			<div class="author">by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=41539&amp;sid=647629669c129e2dd60d55ec27089642">cajundust</a></strong> &raquo; Wed Nov 07, 2012 12:13 pm </div>

			

			<div class="content">Hello,<br /><br />Thanks for the replies.<br />So, the analog video and HDMI cannot be used simultaneously as 2 separate screens.<br /><br />I believe there is already a connector on the type B board, to connect a LCD. But I cannot find any good starters about how and which hardware to connect. Is it also exclusive ? E.g. when connected, the hdmi or analog will not work anymore ?<br /><br />Where can I follow the status ?<br /><br />The other solution, to connect 2 pi's via network, is the last resort solution...</div>

			

		</div>

		
		<dl class="postprofile span3" id="profile210795">
